res←RunAll arg;status;statusCodes;Tests
    ⍝. This function runs all functions beginning with the word 'Test' in the APLSource/Tests folder
    ⍝. Case sensitive 'Test' must be the first word of your test function in order to be executed by this function

    ⍝. Set arguments to Config namespace
    ⎕←'Testing large output file requires WS>8G.'
    ⎕←'Setting ''##.Tests.Config.TestOutputFile←1'' will test 1 million x 4 cells output.'

    ⍝. If non-existent, set up a namespace for holding test configuration, adding certain defaults
    :If (0=⎕NC'##.Tests.Config')
        ##.Tests.Config←⎕NS''
        ##.Tests.Config.TestOutputFile←0
    :EndIf

    ⍝. Run all tests declared, collecting the statuses
    statusCodes←1-⍳4
    status←'PASS' 'FAIL' 'DIDNTRUN' 'ERROR'
    Tests←(⊂'Test'){⍵/⍨⍺{⍺≡4↑⍵}¨⍵}##.Tests.⎕NL ¯3

    res←Tests,⍪{{⍺,≢⍵}⌸,status[statusCodes⍳⍵]}¨Run¨Tests